WRNew year with a difference: South African competitors Braam Malherbe and Peter van Kets make final preparations for the Scott-Amundsen Centenary Race to the South Pole that starts tomorrow. Adventurers from around the globe are expecting weather conditions of -23 C with light snow. Malherbe tweeted of his final preparations: Hectic day. Serious crevasse fields so had to climb very steep slopes with 80&#8201;kg behind, but the beauty lifts my spirit. In awe. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.